<p>The end of your shift is almost here, and you head over to your phone that's charging in the break room, only to find out it wasn't charging that entire time. Your phone battery is incredibly damaged, but it would be too costly to replace it so it constantly needs to be plugged in.</p>\ 

<p>You plug your phone in and have to turn the cord in a specific direction in order for it to work, otherwise it won't charge.</p>\

<p>You head back to the front of the store and watch your last 5 minutes go by with ease. However, once those 5 minutes go by, the person taking over after your shift is [[nowhere in sight|sight]].</p>\

